# Theme and Styling

Import from `@/lib/theme` for all colors, surfaces, borders, shadows, and radius. Never use raw Tailwind color classes (e.g. `bg-gray-50`, `text-blue-600`). The theme module is the single source of truth.

```tsx
import { theme } from '@/lib/theme'
// Use theme.surface, theme.text, theme.border, theme.shadow, theme.radius, theme.status, theme.patterns
className={cn(theme.surface.card, theme.border.default, theme.shadow.sm)}
```

## Theme Module Structure

- `theme.surface` – background, card, muted, mutedSubtle, secondary, popover, input, overlay
- `theme.text` – foreground, muted, primary, success, warning, destructive, info
- `theme.border` – default, subtle, subtleAlt, verySubtle, input, ring, hover
- `theme.shadow` – xs, sm, md, lg, xl
- `theme.radius` – sm, md, lg, full
- `theme.status` – success/warning/destructive/info each with .bg, .border, .text
- `theme.patterns` – inputBase, card, interactive, hoverPrimary

## Shadows

- `shadow-xs` – inputs, selects, form fields
- `shadow-sm` – cards, buttons
- `shadow-md` – dropdowns, popovers
- `shadow-lg` – dialogs
- `shadow-xl` – modals

## Border Radius

- `rounded-md` – default for most components
- `rounded-lg` – larger containers
- `rounded-full` – pills, avatars, icons

## Borders

- `border-border` – default
- `border-border/60` – subtle
- `border-border/40` – very subtle
- Hover: `hover:border-ring`

## Hover States

- Surface: `hover:bg-muted` or `hover:bg-accent`
- Primary emphasis: `hover:bg-primary/10`
- Transitions: `transition-colors` or `transition-[color,box-shadow]`
